	)
	(text_box "Power Pins (From seeedstudio wiki)\n5V - This is 5v out from the USB port. You can also use this as a voltage input but you must have some sort of diode (schottky, signal, power) between your external power source and this pin with anode to battery, cathode to 5V pin.\n3V3 - This is the regulated output from the onboard regulator. You can draw 700mA\nGND - Power/data/signal ground"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -58.42 109.22 0)
		(size 57.15 24.13)
